eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The family of Khayalethu Magadla says they are relieved that he has finally been found. The 6-year-old fell into a manhole at a park in Dlamini, Soweto three weeks ago. READ: Tembe: Search teams faced challenges during search for Khayalethu Magadla His body was found near Eldorado Park Cemetery on Saturday. The family says funeral arrangements will be made once his postmortem is completed. 